<TEXT>
two attackers thought to be leftist 
guerrillas fired rocketpropelled grenades at the us embassy 
wednesday night and an embassy spokesman said the roof was slightly 
damaged but no one was hurt 
the assailants apparently were siding with panamas military in 
its standoff with the united states 
the embassys chief security officer said the assailants fired 
rocketpropelled grenades he spoke on condition his name not be 
used for fear of reprisals 
police initially said rockets were fired at the building from a 
distance of 150 feet witnesses later said they saw men firing a 
recoilless rifle 
the round apparently hit the fence surrounding the embassy and 
exploded prematurely the security officer said we think it 
went off over over the building we went up on the roof and there 
was absolutely no damage 
us embassy spokesman steven gangstead told the associated 
press in a telephone interview that a projectile hit the embassy 
roof causing minor damage but that no injuries resulted 
the attack took place at 805 pm 
the two terrorists fled in a taxi people at a restaurant across 
the street from the embassy told an ap reporter 
anonymous persons calling the bogota television stations 
noticiero nacional and ultimas noticias said the attack was by the 
omar torrijos brigade of a leftist guerrilla group the april 19 
movement also known as the m19 
omar torrijos was head of panamas military at the time he was 
killed in a plane crash in 1981 
gen manuel antonio noriega now head of panamas defense 
forces has been indicted in the united states on drug charges and 
has been resisting us efforts to oust him as military chief he 
is de facto leader of panama 
m19 pamphlets found outside the bogota radio station santa fe 
said the guerrilla attack was because of us intervention in 
panama and the presence of us troops in honduras 
the united states sent 3200 troops to honduras last week after 
honduras said nicaraguan soldiers penetrated honduran territory 
chasing ussupported contra rebels nicaragua denied the charge 
the embassy is in a section of downtown bogota known as the 
bunker for the elaborate security systems designed to protect the 
homes and diplomatic missions in the area 
in washington state department spokeswoman sondra mccarty said 
the agency heard press reports about the attack but she did not 
immediately have any information or comment 
the m19 has claimed responsibility for dozens of bombings 
against us interests in the last 10 years 
bogota police and the army set up roadblocks throughout bogota 
wednesday night trying to catch the terrorists 
drug traffickers opposed to extradition of colombians to the 
united states to face drug charges claimed responsibility for a car 
bomb that exploded alongside the embassy in november 1984 
a woman was killed and six persons were injured all were 
passersby 
