a police officer was indicted by a 
federal grand jury for allegedly pouring scalding water on two 
prisoners at police headquarters last year 
the jury tuesday indicted patrolman christopher dillon on a 
misdemeanor assault charge if convicted he faces a maximum of one 
year in prison and a 25000 fine 
michael c davis and stephen h davis jr and a third man were 
arrested nov 7 after a fight with three other men in providence 
according to us attorney lincoln c almond and assistant us 
attorney edwin j gale 
one of the other three was dillons brother joseph almond said 
after confronting the davises at police headquarters the 
officer poured the water over them with other policemen looking 
on authorities said prosecutors say the men suffered first and 
second degree burns 
