the island habitat has undergone much destruction from goats 
rats and 10inchlong giant centipedes which came in on ships 
in their 3week search clarke and veal will scout two other 
scarce insects only found on st helena a giant ground beetle and 
the st helena dragonfly 
im hoping we will be in time to find the giant earwig and 
save it said clarke 
when asked why anyone should bother he replied everyone asks 
that 
the earwig was part of st helenas life long before we were 
around and it is unqiue as man created the conditions which 
threatened to exterminate it we should try to save it he said 
