to reach a settlement but the parties really did it themselves 
erskine said that pending ratification northwest would suspend 
the contract it was set to impose on april 1 the teamsters agreed 
not to engage in any job action during the ratification process 
the key issue in the dispute was northwests twotier wage 
structure of which the airline had proposed extending the 
lowerpaid scale to eight years from the current five years 
bscale flight attendants argued that the airline was trying to 
break a promise that they would earn higher ascale wages after 
five years 
the issue had intensified since northwest acquired republic 
airlines in 1986 about a third of the 2600 former republic 
attendants are on the lower scale and the others said northwests 
previous wage offer was inadequate 
jeff musto a teamsters spokesman in eagan said only one detail 
of the contract has been disclosed that all flight attendants 
hired by northwest will be required to join the union 
erskine said northwest found no evidence of guerilla warfare 
tactics the union had threatened as a way to keep the company off 
balance 
he also said northwest did not see its traffic diminish during 
the dispute although he acknowledged that some people may have 
booked flights on other airlines 
</TEXT>
