auto parts in the yard or even maintaining a house with most of 
its paint peeling 
provisions banning garbage cans building materials dirt piles 
packing boxes and broken appliances in front yards are part of a 
selfimprovement campaign by the city city officials said 
city councilman dave burton says the city has no business 
subjecting citizens to whiteglove inspections 
this is a sledgehammer approach to a problem of aesthetics 
burton said if you brought a pile of lumber to your house they 
could cite you 
city councilman paul moffatt said the law was needed to prevent 
public health and safety problems arising from the large number of 
people piling refuse in their yards and creating dangerous 
conditions for children in dublin a city of 19000 located 30 
miles southeast of san francisco 
we have old decaying trees where rodents can get in and we 
have some rabies out here said moffatt 
he explained a clothesline could be a hazard if constructed so 
it restricts the vision of a person taking a car around a corner so 
they couldnt negotiate the corner in a safe and orderly manner 
a first violation carries a 100 fine which increases to 500 
for a third infraction before a scofflaw can be charged with a 
misdemeanor and put in jail the ordinance will be enforced only 
when a citizen files a complaint 
