six israeli warplanes today rocketed 
palestinian guerrilla bases on the outskirts of this southern port 
city 
thick black smoke billowed from the stricken targets southeast 
of sidon 25 miles south of beirut as the fighterbombers struck 
shortly after 4 pm lebanese police said 
the israeli military said the targets were buildings used by 
guerrillas for storing weapons and equipment it said the buildings 
were also used as garages for the guerrillas vehicles 
there were no immediate figures on casualties police said 
several ambulances raced with sirens wailing from sidon to pick up 
victims 
the israeli announcement did not identify which guerrilla group 
had been attacked israel radios arabic service quoted beirut 
radio stations as saying the targets belonged to yasser arafats 
fatah guerrillas and lebanese moslem militias 
the army said that all the planes returned safely to their bases 
and that the pilots reported that the targets were destroyed 
the army said israeli planes also destroyed a vehicle equipped 
with antiaircraft guns 
police said the planes fired at least 25 rockets in five runs on 
guerrilla bases in a cluster of villages near sidons ein elhilweh 
refugee camp 
they said the pilots released air balloons to deflect 
heatseeking sam7 missiles unleashed by guerrillas 
the air strike was the second against the palestinians in a week 
and the fourth this year thirtyone people were killed and 43 
wounded in the three previous israeli air raids this year 
