by 1973 174000 refugees returned to pakistan but the 
repatriation ended abruptly when funds ran out stranding 250000 
people about 100000 are believed to have returned since but the 
rest remain in refugee camps in bangladesh 
bangladesh foreign secretary nazrul islam told reporters 
