<TEXT>
northwest airlines said today it will ban 
smoking on all of its domestic flights except to and from hawaii 
making it the first major us airline to mandate a smokefree 
travel environment in the air 
the restrictions will begin on april 23 the same day a federal 
law is to go into effect banning smoking on all domestic flights of 
two hours or less 
northwest noted in a statement that its program goes 
significantly beyond the requirements of the new law 
in addition to flights within the contiguous 48 states the 
program dubbed northwest clears the air will apply to flights 
to and from alaska mexico canada jamaica and the cayman islands 
flights to hawaii and ovrseas will continue to offer smoking 
sections because those flights carry a greater proportion of 
foreign passengers who feel differently about the issue the 
airline said in a statement 
ab magary the airlines executive vice president for 
marketing said a majority of passengers on international flights 
are foreign and are not yet culturally ready to move in this 
direction 
he said the ban is a response to our customers and employees 
requests a northwest study showed that nine out of 10 passengers 
prefer to sit in the nosmoking section of a plane 
magary said however that the airline is not going 
macrobiotic the ban does not imply some broaderscale effort 
to rid the united states of cigarettes he said 
northwest said it will offer refunds to passengers who purchased 
tickets before today and who have been assigned seats in the 
smoking section if they decline to fly because of the new policy 
travel agents on tuesday complimented northwest on its plans 
were hearing from our customers that its time to go more 
toward banning said jay harrington regional president of 
uniglobe a national chain of travel agency franchises we think 
its inevitable it will be banned on all aircraft 
in the short run he said northwest might lose some customers 
who smoke heavily but generally passengers choose flights on the 
basis of convenience and price 
air canada which banned smoking on some flights between canada 
and the united states said it gained customers as a result of its 
nosmoking policy 
northwest would have had to eliminate smoking on many of its 
flights anyway because about 80 percent of all us flights last 
two hours or less 
by extending the ban to all flights northwest could be avoiding 
confusion expected to result from the new law for example it was 
not clear how the law would apply to flights that are scheduled to 
take under two hours but are delayed 
more important northwest could be saving itself some costs 
airlines must install and maintain filters that are difficult and 
costly to clean and they spend additional money on air 
conditioning to recirculate fresh air 
the new law part of a spending bill signed by president reagan 
in december is a compromise version of nosmoking bills that the 
house and senate passed earlier the federal ban will last for two 
years smoking cigars and pipes already is prohibited on airlines 
under the new law passengers who insist on lighting up will 
face civil fines of as much as 1000 and passengers who tamper 
with smoke alarms in airplane lavatories will be liable for as much 
as 2000 in penalties 
northwest airlines said it would launch an advertising campaign 
to promote the program on saturday 
attending northwests press conference were representatives of 
the us surgeon generals office the american cancer society the 
american heart association and the american lung association 
james swamley managing director of the american lung 
association credited northwest with jetting ahead of the 
industry 
separately singapore airlines unveiled plans to introduce the 
first nosmoking commercial flights in southeast asia next month 
four of the 14 daily shuttle flights between singapore and kuala 
lumpur the capital of neighboring malaysia will bar smoking 
starting april 4 said a news release from the 
governmentcontrolled carrier the trip takes about 45 minutes 
</TEXT>
