intel corp said today it will sell computer 
memory chips made by micron technology inc and has received a 
warrant to buy stock in the boise idahobased chip maker 
the deal with intel one of the nations biggest independent 
chip makers should give micron some longterm stability in the 
volatile business 
micron is one of only two us companies along with texas 
instruments inc that have withstood competition from japan to 
continue producing the common chips known as dynamic random access 
memories drams 
the computer and electronics industry has been hampered in 
recent months by a severe shortage of computer memory chips the 
intelmicron deal will initially apply only to 256k drams the 
generation of chips that is gradually being replaced by the more 
powerful 1megabit drams 
intel which dropped out of the dram business several years 
ago said it received a warrant from micron to purchase 600000 
shares of micron stock at an exercise price of 1937 a share 
that would represent less than 3 percent of microns stock 
microns stock rose to 2112 a share in overthecounter 
